00:24.989 --> 00:28.049
<i>[ Whistle Blowing ]</i>

00:30.527 --> 00:32.427
[ Beeping ]

00:38.168 --> 00:40.068
## [Jazzy Solo ]

01:00.157 --> 01:02.057
[ Beeping ]

01:02.159 --> 01:04.059
[ Tires Screeching ]

01:05.429 --> 01:07.397
D'oh!
[ Screams ]

01:09.133 --> 01:13.126
- [ Electricity Crackling ]
- [ Grunting, Groaning ]

01:27.985 --> 01:31.512
Now remember. We have
to leave nature just the way we found it.

01:31.622 --> 01:33.817
Everything we pack in, we pack out.

01:33.924 --> 01:37.189
- What if I have to do my business?
- Use this plastic bag.

01:37.294 --> 01:40.320
Aw, how come bears can
crap in the woods and I can't?

01:42.433 --> 01:43.764
[ Growling ]

01:46.270 --> 01:50.934
Ah, we're so lucky to have this untouched
piece of paradise so close to Springfield.

01:52.276 --> 01:54.176
<i>- [ Droning ]
- [ Gasps ] Bees!</i>

01:54.278 --> 01:56.974
They sound angry and Africanized.

01:57.081 --> 01:59.709
Okay, nobody panic.
There's plenty of spray for me.

02:01.118 --> 02:03.143
<i>[ Droning Continues ]</i>

02:03.253 --> 02:06.154
<i>[ Engines Humming, Tires Screeching ]</i>

02:06.256 --> 02:08.781
That doesn't sound like bees.

02:08.892 --> 02:11.360
Oh, my God.

02:11.462 --> 02:13.760
It's a racetrack!

02:13.864 --> 02:16.332
[ Gasps ]
The bird sanctuary!

02:16.433 --> 02:19.459
<i>- They ruined it!
- [ Homer] No, they didn't!</i>

02:19.570 --> 02:22.437
They just surrounded it with
something wonderful!

02:22.539 --> 02:24.598
Like a raisin covered in chocolate.

02:24.708 --> 02:27.233
Or a monkey in a cowboy suit.

02:29.279 --> 02:31.770
[ All Gasp ]

02:31.882 --> 02:33.782
[ All Gasp ]

02:35.619 --> 02:38.247
See? Animals can
get used to anything.

02:38.355 --> 02:41.722
[ Growling, Chittering ]

02:41.825 --> 02:43.884
[ Squawks ]
Start your engines.

02:43.994 --> 02:46.053
Show us your boobs.
Show us your boobs.

02:46.163 --> 02:48.358
[ Grunts ]
You better do what he says, Marge.

02:52.803 --> 02:56.705
<i>Cool. Way to adapt, little guy.</i>

02:58.175 --> 03:01.303
Why do jerks think everyone
wants to see their stupid name?

03:03.781 --> 03:06.147
[ Tires Screeching ]

03:06.250 --> 03:08.718
- [ Munching Loudly ]
- [ Screams ]

03:10.954 --> 03:12.854
Sorry to break up
your picnic, folks.

03:12.956 --> 03:16.653
- I'm two-time fast-car champ, Clay Babcock.
- You're on fire!

03:16.760 --> 03:19.786
Yeah, I have won a lot of races.
It's all thanks to my crew, really.

03:19.897 --> 03:21.797
[ Grunts ]
There it is.

03:21.899 --> 03:23.457
Mr. Babcock, can I ride in your car?

03:23.567 --> 03:26.832
Well, my ''A'' car was just incinerated,
but, uh, you can ride in my ''B'' car.

03:26.937 --> 03:29.997
- [ Flame Roars ]
- I don't see why not.

03:31.375 --> 03:33.275
Bart, these are the ''time trials''...

03:33.377 --> 03:35.345
that determine the ''pole position.''

03:35.446 --> 03:37.175
Shouldn't you be keeping
your hands on the wheel?

03:37.281 --> 03:40.409
Oh, sure, if you want to drive
the ''traditional'' way.

03:40.517 --> 03:42.417
- [ Grinding Metal ]
- Sorry.

03:42.519 --> 03:44.987
Boy, these cars
are surprisingly roomy.

03:45.089 --> 03:47.887
Yeah, we like to bring our families along
on the longer races.

03:47.991 --> 03:50.960
If I get tired, I let my wife drive.
She's good.

03:51.061 --> 03:53.325
Get your feet off the upholstery!

03:53.430 --> 03:55.523
[ Engine Slows ]

03:55.632 --> 03:58.465
I got some spare tickets
if you'd like to stick around for the race.

03:58.569 --> 04:01.663
That's very sweet,
but we have a full day of hiking planned.

04:01.772 --> 04:03.672
We can hike anytime.

04:03.774 --> 04:06.106
- This is our chance to see cars driving.
- [ Sighs ]

04:06.210 --> 04:08.576
<i>[ Engines Roar]</i>

04:09.680 --> 04:11.705
Hi-diddly-ho,
pedal-to-the-metal-o-philes.

04:11.815 --> 04:14.511
Flanders! Since when
do you like anything cool?

04:14.618 --> 04:16.517
Well, I don't care for the speed...

04:16.620 --> 04:18.519
but I can't get enough
of that safety gear-

04:18.622 --> 04:20.522
Helmets, roll bars, caution flags.

04:20.624 --> 04:24.321
I like the fresh air and looking
at the poor people in the infield.

04:24.428 --> 04:26.396
[ Cheering ]

04:26.497 --> 04:29.022
- [ Moaning ]
- Dang, Cletus.

04:29.133 --> 04:31.033
Why'd you have to park
by my parents?

04:31.135 --> 04:33.968
Now, honey, they's my parents too.

04:34.071 --> 04:36.062
- ## [ Riff]
- [ Chuckles ]

04:36.173 --> 04:41.042
<i>- [ Announcer] Gentlemen, start your engines.
- [ Engines Roar]</i>

04:41.145 --> 04:44.342
- Daddy, can we move closer?
- Abso-not-ly, hot Roddy.

04:44.448 --> 04:47.008
We're up here out of range of the crashes
and the drivers' cussin'.

04:47.117 --> 04:49.017
- Move your damn butt.
- Bite me.

04:53.557 --> 04:54.683
[ All Gasp ]

04:56.260 --> 04:57.784
[ All Groan ]

04:58.896 --> 05:01.558
<i>[ All Gasp, Groan ]</i>

05:01.665 --> 05:03.929
Come on! Somebody crash!

05:04.034 --> 05:08.300
Be patient, Son.
A watched car never crashes.

05:08.405 --> 05:10.532
<i>- [ Car Crashes ]
- Oh, I missed one!</i>

05:10.641 --> 05:13.769
- [ Engines Roar]
- Let's go! Let's go!

05:17.014 --> 05:18.641
The dice!
The dice! The dice!

05:21.285 --> 05:23.253
Eight seconds.
Great job, boys!

05:24.321 --> 05:26.221
[ Engine Sputters, Backfires ]

05:29.126 --> 05:31.060
Let's go. New tires.
Come on. Come on.

05:31.161 --> 05:34.358
We're goin' as fast as we can, m-
Hey, who are you?

05:34.464 --> 05:36.932
- Oh, how rude of me. My name is-
- [ Tires Squeal ]

05:40.003 --> 05:41.368
My bad.

05:41.471 --> 05:44.838
[ Announcer]
And now here's something for the guys.

05:44.942 --> 05:46.136
Finally.

05:46.243 --> 05:51.442
<i>Let's hear it for...
Fan-demonium!</i>

05:51.548 --> 05:56.747
Hey, racing fans.
Who wants a free T-shirt?

05:56.853 --> 05:58.514
- [ Cheering ]
- Me! Me!

05:58.622 --> 06:01.853
<i>- ;'Aqui! Aqui!
- I do! I do!</i>

06:01.959 --> 06:04.154
Wait. No, I don't.

06:08.799 --> 06:12.064
Hmm. A Ford urinating on a Chevrolet.

06:12.169 --> 06:16.572
- Don't you usually laugh at everything?
- Yes. Yes, I do.

06:16.673 --> 06:19.540
- Come on! Right here! [ Screams ]
- [ Gasping ]

06:19.643 --> 06:22.441
- I'm okay, folks.
- [ All Groan ]

06:22.546 --> 06:24.776
I need a shirt!
Give me a shirt!

06:24.881 --> 06:27.975
- Mommy has bosoms like that.
- [ Chuckles ] Yeah, I wish.

06:28.085 --> 06:31.987
Neddie, I've had about
all I can take of Homer Simpson's torso.

06:32.089 --> 06:34.455
- I'll get some hot dogs.
- No foot-longs.

06:34.558 --> 06:37.789
I know.
They make you uncomfortable.

06:37.894 --> 06:41.921
<i>Well, I guess no one else
wants a T-shirt.</i>

06:42.032 --> 06:45.229
That's a damn lie, and you know it!
Gimme a shirt!

06:45.335 --> 06:47.633
You heard him, girls.

06:49.773 --> 06:52.936
Hey, T-shirt, T-shirt, T-shirt.

06:53.043 --> 06:55.443
Fire!

06:55.545 --> 06:57.240
Ooh, a bobby pin!

06:58.315 --> 07:00.476
<i>- [ Screams ]
- [ Thuds ]</i>

07:00.584 --> 07:02.848
[ Gasps ]
Maude?

07:03.787 --> 07:06.654
[ Murmuring ]

07:06.757 --> 07:09.783
Oh, my Lord, she's dead!

07:09.893 --> 07:11.952
[ Groans ]

07:15.532 --> 07:19.059
It's hard to believe
we're never going to see Maude again.

07:19.169 --> 07:22.229
And poor Ned
didn't get a chance to say good-bye.

07:22.339 --> 07:24.671
Well, from now on,
I'm never gonna let you leave the room...

07:24.775 --> 07:28.233
without telling you how much I love you,
and how truly special-

07:28.345 --> 07:31.212
This is eating up a lot of time.
Maybe just a pat on the butt.

07:31.315 --> 07:33.215
- [ Light Smack ]
- Yeah, that works.

07:33.317 --> 07:38.550
Now, Homie, you know, Ned and the boys
need us. And you know what that means.

07:38.655 --> 07:42.716
- I know. No more being a jerk.
- That's right.

07:42.826 --> 07:45.021
[ Sniffles ]

07:56.373 --> 08:01.310
In many ways, Maude Flanders
was a supporting player in our lives.

08:01.411 --> 08:05.541
She didn't grab our attention
with memorable catchphrases...

08:05.649 --> 08:07.617
or comical accents.

08:07.718 --> 08:09.151
- Aye.
- Yarr.

08:09.252 --> 08:11.846
Oh, glavin!
Why, glavin?

08:11.955 --> 08:17.325
But, whether you noticed her or not,
Maude was always there.

08:17.427 --> 08:20.021
And we thought she always would be.

08:20.130 --> 08:22.758
My friends, life is about change.

08:22.866 --> 08:26.097
Just yesterday,
Apu was a lonely bachelor.

08:26.203 --> 08:29.434
- [ Crying ]
- Yes, thank God those days are over.

08:29.539 --> 08:33.339
And the Van Houtens
were enjoying a storybook marriage.

08:33.443 --> 08:36.207
Yeah. Lots of storybooks
have witches.

08:36.313 --> 08:37.940
- Shut up, Kirk!
- [ Quickly ] Sorry.

08:38.048 --> 08:41.313
And now, the good people at Fan-demonium,
as part of a generous settlement...

08:41.418 --> 08:43.909
will fire a 21 T-shirt salute.

08:44.955 --> 08:46.855
[ Cocking Air Guns ]

08:46.957 --> 08:50.916
<i>##[ Bagpipe.' ''Amazing Grace'']</i>

08:54.865 --> 08:56.059
Finally.

09:03.039 --> 09:06.372
Ned, my friend, please know
that the Kwik-E-Mart is there for you...

09:06.476 --> 09:09.741
<i>- 2 4 hours a day.
- Oh, thank you, Apu.</i>

09:09.846 --> 09:13.441
And I'm going to give you
all of Maude's frequent Squishy points.

09:13.550 --> 09:15.541
The boys at headquarters
will not like it...

09:15.652 --> 09:18.280
but I'm getting pretty sick of
them and their Bombay attitude!

09:18.388 --> 09:21.516
That's enough there, Apu. Look, Ned,
I know we ain't hung out much...

09:21.625 --> 09:23.786
what with your insane
fear of drinking...

09:23.894 --> 09:25.794
and me being banned
from the church and all...

09:25.896 --> 09:28.421
but, uh, but that Maude,
she was really somethin'.

09:28.532 --> 09:31.057
Oh, wasn't she?
Thank you, Moe. I appreciate that.

09:31.168 --> 09:35.366
Oh, I really mean it though. I mean, if it was
you that died, I would've been on her so fast!

09:35.472 --> 09:38.066
- What are you saying?
- What? Nothing. She was hot.

09:38.175 --> 09:40.336
- What? You can't take a compliment?
- Hot?

09:40.444 --> 09:42.503
You monster!
[ Grunting ]

09:42.612 --> 09:45.342
That's good. No.
Let it out. That's it. Let it out.

09:45.449 --> 09:49.408
Send me to Maude. That's it.
Here I come, baby. Oh, yeah!

09:52.856 --> 09:56.883
Bart, honey, I think you should
go play with Rod and Todd.

09:59.262 --> 10:02.527
Oh, man. Why does everything bad
have to happen to me?

10:02.632 --> 10:06.227
<i>When I'm feeling low,
you know what always cheers me up?</i>

10:06.336 --> 10:09.134
- Is it love?
- Kindness?

10:09.239 --> 10:13.198
Ooh, tough room.
Video games. What do you got?

10:13.310 --> 10:15.244
<i>Billy Graham's Bible Blaster?</i>

10:16.346 --> 10:18.712
Keep firing!
Convert the heathens!

10:18.815 --> 10:20.783
## [ ''Bringing in the Sheaves'' ]

10:23.353 --> 10:26.413
- Got him!
- No, you just winged him
and made him a Unitarian.

10:26.523 --> 10:28.991
Look out, Bart! A gentle Baha'i.

10:29.092 --> 10:33.085
- ## [ Fanfare ]
- All right! Full conversion!

10:33.196 --> 10:35.187
Thanks, guys.
This really cheered me up.

10:35.298 --> 10:37.198
[ Man ]
Second Coming! Reload! Reload!

10:37.300 --> 10:40.633
- Can we play now?
- You are playing. We're a team.

10:42.172 --> 10:44.231
[ Together]
Yea!

10:46.476 --> 10:50.139
Now, if there's anything,
anything at all I can do to help out.

10:50.247 --> 10:52.477
Quit hogging Flanders.
I want to comfort him.

10:52.582 --> 10:57.144
[ Chuckles ] That's nice of you, Homer,
but I think I'll just go to bed.

10:57.254 --> 10:59.722
Then I insist on walking you home.

10:59.823 --> 11:01.814
Homer, this really isn't necessary.

11:01.925 --> 11:03.825
Those feelings are normal, Ned.

11:03.927 --> 11:06.418
They're part of the process.
Watch the sprinkler.

11:06.530 --> 11:10.330
- Hey! That's my sprinkler.
- It's natural to feel that way.

11:10.433 --> 11:13.061
But the sprinkler is gone.
It's time to let go.

11:13.169 --> 11:14.796
I just bought that.

11:14.905 --> 11:17.669
I know. I know.
It's never easy.

11:17.774 --> 11:19.935
You want anything else?
Water? Chili fries?

11:20.043 --> 11:21.943
How about some white noise?
[ Hisses ]

11:22.045 --> 11:26.072
Oh, Homer. You don't... have to-
[ Snoring ]

11:28.818 --> 11:30.649
Sleep tight, Neddie.

11:38.528 --> 11:41.053
- [ Tapping On Glass ]
- [ Groans ] What is that?

11:42.299 --> 11:45.132
Oh, you wanna rock fight, eh?

11:45.235 --> 11:48.068
- [ Laughs ]
- No, Homer. I just need to talk.

11:48.171 --> 11:50.867
Okay. Be right down.

11:50.974 --> 11:52.874
[ Chuckles ]

11:52.976 --> 11:56.275
I just keep replaying
the whole thing in my head.

11:56.379 --> 12:01.316
I can't believe my last words to Maude
were, ''No foot-longs.''

12:01.418 --> 12:03.579
Yep. It would have been a lot
better if you'd said...

12:03.687 --> 12:05.587
''I love you'' or, ''You're special.''

12:05.689 --> 12:08.021
You know, something sweet
instead of that hot dog crack.

12:08.124 --> 12:12.151
If I'd only been a gentlemen
and got the hot dogs myself...

12:12.262 --> 12:14.162
she'd still be here.

12:14.264 --> 12:16.391
Now, now, now.
Don't beat yourself up.

12:16.499 --> 12:18.524
I'm the one who drove her
out of her seat.

12:18.635 --> 12:21.570
I'm the one who provoked
the lethal barrage ofT-shirts.

12:21.671 --> 12:25.903
I'm the one who parked in the ambulance zone,
preventing any possible resuscitation.

12:26.009 --> 12:29.035
Uh, but there's no point
in playing the blame game.

12:29.145 --> 12:32.945
Ah, you're right.
I just gotta work through the grief.

12:33.049 --> 12:35.040
There's not gonna be an easy answer.

12:35.151 --> 12:37.085
Easy answer, eh?

12:41.725 --> 12:44.592
Oh, yeah. That's it, baby.
That's the money shot.

12:44.694 --> 12:48.858
<i>Yeah, the camera loves you. Oh,you tease,you.
[ Chuckles ]</i>

12:48.965 --> 12:51.866
- Why are you taping Flanders, Dad?
- You'll see.

12:51.968 --> 12:53.560
Do you even have a job anymore?

12:53.670 --> 12:56.537
I think it's pretty obvious
that I don't!

12:57.774 --> 13:00.038
Okay, I finished
the gardening sequence.

13:00.143 --> 13:04.842
Okay, from here we star wipe to
a glamour shot of Flanders paying his bills.

13:04.948 --> 13:07.542
<i>Then we star wipe to Flanders
brushing his-</i>

13:07.651 --> 13:11.018
Dad, there are other wipes
besides star wipes.

13:11.121 --> 13:13.248
Why eat hamburger
when you can have steak?

13:13.356 --> 13:15.256
I'm taking my name off this thing.

13:16.760 --> 13:19.388
- So, how you doin', Ned?
- Oh, it's been a hard couple of months...

13:19.496 --> 13:21.396
but I feel like
I've turned a corner.

13:21.498 --> 13:24.797
Well, that's all gonna change,
thanks to this tape!

13:24.901 --> 13:27.233
- Tape?
- Now the audio needs some tweaking...

13:27.337 --> 13:30.067
and there's some footage of Maggie
being born that I couldn't get rid of.

13:30.173 --> 13:32.368
<i>- Anyway, enjoy.
- [ Tape Loading ]</i>

13:32.475 --> 13:34.375
[ Homer's Voice ]
Single women of Springfield...

13:34.477 --> 13:37.969
-your prayers have been ''Flanswered''.
- ## [ Fanfare ]

13:38.081 --> 13:39.981
Ned Flanswered, that is.

13:40.083 --> 13:42.278
- Is this a dating video?
- Shush!

13:42.385 --> 13:46.685
<i>What would you say about a man who
owns his own house and his own car?</i>

13:46.790 --> 13:49.918
That's Ned Flanders!

13:50.026 --> 13:52.722
A man who's not afraid to cry.

13:52.829 --> 13:54.729
- Hey, Ned!
- [ Sobs ]

13:54.831 --> 13:58.198
- So that's why you maced me.
- [ Chuckles ] Yeah.

13:58.301 --> 14:00.201
<i>Ned does everything with class.</i>

14:00.303 --> 14:02.498
Whether he's punching in
his A.T.M. code...

14:03.973 --> 14:06.703
or keeping clean in the shower.

14:06.810 --> 14:09.335
<i>- Homer!
- But don't take my word for it.</i>

14:09.446 --> 14:11.573
<i>Listen to this testimonial.</i>

14:11.681 --> 14:14.878
Oh, I would date Ned in a second
if I was a woman or gay.

14:14.984 --> 14:17.976
He looks like a cuddler,
that Ned. I-I like that.

14:18.088 --> 14:20.648
I like to be held.
I like to be pampered.

14:27.297 --> 14:27.888
step up to the best.

14:27.997 --> 14:32.127
Ned Flanders, the man with the chest.

14:32.235 --> 14:35.602
[ Panting, Grunting ]

14:35.705 --> 14:36.831
Ew!

14:36.940 --> 14:39.408
Now we'll just send this
to the dating service...

14:39.509 --> 14:41.534
the chicks'll fall for you, and bam!

14:41.644 --> 14:43.544
The healing begins.

14:43.646 --> 14:47.844
Uh, Homer, you obviously
went to a lot of trouble, but dating?

14:47.951 --> 14:50.044
It just feels way too soon.

14:50.153 --> 14:52.451
[ Chuckles ]
That's great!

14:52.555 --> 14:54.455
Chicks really dig sensitivity.

14:54.557 --> 14:56.491
- Did you get that, Bart?
- Got it.

14:56.593 --> 15:00.029
Beautiful.
And star wipe, and we're out.

15:00.130 --> 15:01.995
Hmm.

15:03.733 --> 15:06.531
Well, with triple word score,
that's 90.

15:06.636 --> 15:10.265
[ Laughs ]
I guess my luck is starting to even out.

15:10.373 --> 15:12.773
[ Sighs ]
I'm just a ''Q'' without a ''U''.

15:12.876 --> 15:15.140
Mmm.

15:27.390 --> 15:29.290
[ Chuckles ]

15:29.392 --> 15:34.955
[ Laughs ]
Uh, hello? Mailman?

15:39.402 --> 15:42.371
These are the women who
saw your videotape and are interested.

15:42.472 --> 15:45.600
And feel free to root around
in the one-nighter bin.

15:45.708 --> 15:48.700
- The bin is spoken for.
- Are you gonna call all those women?

15:48.812 --> 15:51.440
No, the tapes will do just fine.
Thank you.

15:51.548 --> 15:55.314
Homer, I'm having second thoughts.
This feels so disloyal to Maude.

15:55.418 --> 15:58.717
Oh, wake up, Ned.
You think Maude isn't dating in heaven?

15:58.822 --> 16:01.017
- You think she would?
- How could she not?

16:01.124 --> 16:03.149
The place is full
of eligible bachelors.

16:03.259 --> 16:06.990
John Wayne, Tupac Shakur,
Sherlock Holmes.

16:07.096 --> 16:09.223
[ Chuckles ]
Sherlock Holmes is a character.

16:09.332 --> 16:11.533
[ Chuckles ] He sure is.
[ Growls ]

16:11.771 --> 16:13.271
Okay Here goes nothing

16:14.571 --> 16:15.871
If you select me

16:16.072 --> 16:19.005
you'll get a lot more than
a Wharton M.B.A. pulling in 200 K.

16:19.309 --> 16:21.971
You'll get a woman
who's poised, articulate...

16:22.078 --> 16:24.979
sophisticated, confident
and highly sexual.

16:25.081 --> 16:27.481
Hang on.
I'm getting a fax.

16:27.584 --> 16:29.552
Damn, I've just been indicted.

16:29.652 --> 16:32.143
Looks like we're gonna have to reschedule.
How's your July?

16:32.255 --> 16:34.815
- Well, I-
- Mine's terrible. Let's talk in August.

16:34.924 --> 16:37.051
[ Sighs ]

16:38.127 --> 16:41.824
Mmm. Dinner was delicious, Edna.

16:41.931 --> 16:46.630
But I can't shake the feeling that you're
just using me to get Principal Skinner jealous.

16:46.736 --> 16:51.366
Oh, please. I don't care
what Mr. ''Engaged to be Engaged'' thinks.

16:51.474 --> 16:52.941
Hear that, Seymour?

16:53.042 --> 16:55.408
- [ Skinner] Edna, this is childish.
- Fine, then hang up.

16:55.511 --> 16:58.571
<i>- I will hang up when he leaves.
- [ Sighs ]</i>

16:58.681 --> 17:03.948
Well, Diane, I've sure enjoyed chatting with you
about your problems with your mother.

17:04.053 --> 17:08.012
Did you hear that, Foofie?
Sounds like somebody ''wuvs'' us.

17:08.124 --> 17:10.558
<i>- Yes, it does.
- [ Chuckles ] Yeah.</i>

17:10.660 --> 17:12.560
Well, maybe
I'll call you again sometime.

17:12.662 --> 17:16.290
Ooh. Foofie doesn't like
the sound of that ''maybe.''

17:16.398 --> 17:20.096
'Cause him's a commitment dog,
isn't him?

17:20.203 --> 17:22.933
[ Gasping, Panting ]

17:26.643 --> 17:28.542
So, how'd you do tonight, Romeo?

17:28.645 --> 17:31.614
Well, I just can't relate
to the women of today, Homer.

17:31.714 --> 17:35.241
Ah, it's probably me.
I'm about as exciting as a baked potato.

17:35.351 --> 17:39.720
You're darn right you are! And you've got
lots of other great qualities too!

17:39.822 --> 17:44.156
That's right, Ned. Those floozies we married
in Vegas were crazy about you.

17:44.260 --> 17:46.228
What floozies?
What are you talking-

17:46.329 --> 17:48.559
Marge! We're trying to help Ned!

17:48.665 --> 17:51.190
Lord, I never question you...

17:51.301 --> 17:56.705
but I've been wondering if your decision
to take Maude was, well, wrong.

17:56.806 --> 17:59.570
U-Unless this is part of
your divine plan.

17:59.676 --> 18:02.270
[ Clicks Tongue ]
Could you just give me some kind of sign?

18:04.047 --> 18:06.379
Anything?

18:06.482 --> 18:09.576
Aw, and after all that
church chocolate I bought...

18:09.686 --> 18:14.885
which, by the way,
was gritty and had that white stuff on it!

18:14.991 --> 18:17.687
Well, I've had it!

18:22.398 --> 18:25.390
Daddy, get up.
You'll be late for church.

18:25.501 --> 18:28.265
Well, you boys can go with the Simpsons.
I'm not going to church today.

18:28.371 --> 18:30.339
- [ Gasps ]
- That's right.

18:30.440 --> 18:32.340
And I may not go to church tomorrow.

18:32.442 --> 18:34.910
[ Whimpering, Screaming ]

18:35.011 --> 18:39.345
No, I'm not kiddin'!
I am gonna sit right here and miss church.

18:39.449 --> 18:43.044
You just watch.

18:43.152 --> 18:44.676
Sorry! Sorry! Sorry! Sorry!
Sorry! Sorry!

18:45.888 --> 18:49.756
While our organist
is on a much-needed vacation...

18:49.859 --> 18:51.759
we thought we'd try something new.

18:51.861 --> 18:56.355
So get down and put your knees together
for the Christian rock stylings of...

18:57.400 --> 19:01.234
- Kovenant!
- ## [ Rock ]

19:01.337 --> 19:03.965
Hey, isn't that the bass player
from Satanica?

19:04.073 --> 19:05.973
I think it is.

19:10.013 --> 19:12.413
<i>- ##[ Continues ]
- [ Gasps ] Electric guitars in church!</i>

19:12.515 --> 19:16.076
Oh, my gosh. Some dropouts must have
overpowered the reverend.

19:19.389 --> 19:22.415
This is a love song about a dude I met
in a sleazy motel.

19:22.525 --> 19:24.925
- [ Gasps ]
- A dude named God.

19:25.028 --> 19:26.928
Oh.

19:27.030 --> 19:30.625
# In a motel room
in Delacroix #

19:30.733 --> 19:33.031
# I was drinking like
