19:33.136 --> 19:37.095
-#And thinking 'bout the wrong turns that I took #
-[ Snoring ]

19:37.206 --> 19:40.232
#Well, I woke up
on the puke-green floor #

19:40.343 --> 19:42.675
#And opened up
a dresser drawer #

19:42.779 --> 19:46.875
# Lookin' for a bottle
but instead, I found a book #

19:46.983 --> 19:48.883
She's talking about the Bible.

19:48.985 --> 19:51.215
- So? She's good-lookin'. Shut up.
- You shut up.

19:53.056 --> 19:55.456
#A book about a man #

19:55.558 --> 19:57.856
#A book about the dude
who lives above #

19:57.960 --> 20:00.019
#A book about a man #

20:00.129 --> 20:04.589
#Who drives a pickup full
of sweet, sweet love #

20:04.700 --> 20:06.964
- ## [ Humming ]
- [ Clattering ]

20:08.104 --> 20:10.299
# Now if you think
he doesn't care #

20:10.406 --> 20:12.704
# Or maybe that he isn't there #

20:12.809 --> 20:17.212
<i>#It's not too late
to see how wrong you are #</i>

20:17.313 --> 20:19.975
# So when your soul
has gone astray #

20:20.083 --> 20:22.244
#Just let God be your triple A #

20:22.351 --> 20:24.251
# He'll tow you to salvation #

20:24.353 --> 20:28.221
#And he'll overhaul your heart ##

20:31.894 --> 20:33.589
Glad you made it, Ned.

20:33.696 --> 20:36.130
I knew he would!

20:37.233 --> 20:38.962
[ Grunts ]

20:39.068 --> 20:42.731
I'll be right back, boys.
I've gotta go help that lady.

20:42.839 --> 20:46.935
- Homer, you help too.
- I toileth not on ye Sabbath, woman!

20:47.043 --> 20:48.977
- A pox on thee!
- [ Groans ]

20:50.813 --> 20:53.907
- [ Grunts ]
- [ Grunts ]

20:54.016 --> 20:56.450
[ Sighs ]
That was a lovely song.

20:56.552 --> 21:00.147
- It really got to me.
- Been through some rough times yourself?

21:00.256 --> 21:02.190
I-I recently lost my wife.

21:02.291 --> 21:06.159
[ Gasps ] I'm real sorry to hear that.
We just lost our drummer...

21:06.262 --> 21:08.059
to a Pentecostal ska band.

21:08.164 --> 21:10.064
I know it's not the same-

21:10.166 --> 21:13.226
No, I hear what you're saying.
It's always hard to replace someone.

21:13.336 --> 21:16.066
Yeah. My name's RachelJordan.

21:16.172 --> 21:19.039
If you feel like talking,
maybe we could grab a coffee?

21:19.142 --> 21:21.170
Well, that- that sounds
real nice, Rachel...

21:21.278 --> 21:24.042
but I'm, uh, I'm not quite-

21:24.247 --> 21:26.047
I understand.

21:26.749 --> 21:30.048
Listen. We're heading out on tour
with the Monsters of Christian Rock.

21:30.153 --> 21:32.451
Maybe when we get back,
you and I could get together.

21:32.555 --> 21:35.547
[ Chuckles ]
Maybe we can. My name's Ned Flanders.

21:35.658 --> 21:39.118
And I'm here every week,
rain or shine.

